Data input

Lets check how the data looks like and what the objectives of the analyses are.

We conclude that we have data for two cell lines, in two different passages each. Each was measured for the abundance of 146 different analytes between two treatments. These are however always a little bit different.

treat1<-read_delim(file = "../raw_data/counts_B_P_U_screen/P1_S7_L001_R1_001.txt",delim = "\t")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   sgRNA = col_character(),
##   Count = col_double()
## )
treat2<-read_delim(file = "../raw_data/counts_B_P_U_screen/P2_S8_L001_R1_001.txt",delim = "\t")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   sgRNA = col_character(),
##   Count = col_double()
## )
treatment<-"P"

system(paste("mkdir",treatment))

dmso1<-read_delim(file = "../raw_data/counts_B_P_U_screen/DMSO1_S1_L001_R1_001.txt",delim = "\t")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   sgRNA = col_character(),
##   Count = col_double()
## )
dmso2<-read_delim(file = "../raw_data/counts_B_P_U_screen/DMSO2_S2_L001_R1_001.txt",delim = "\t")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   sgRNA = col_character(),
##   Count = col_double()
## )
mydata<-treat1 %>% 
  left_join(treat2,by="sgRNA") %>% 
  left_join(dmso1,by="sgRNA") %>% 
  left_join(dmso2,by="sgRNA") %>%
  extract(sgRNA,c("sgRNA","gene_id"),"((\\w+)_.*)") 

names(mydata)<-c("sgRNA","gene_id","treat_1","treat_2","dmso_1","dmso_2")

mydata %<>%
  gather(treatment,count,-sgRNA,-gene_id) %>%
  extract(treatment,c("treatment","replicate"),"(\\w+)_(\\d)")

anno<-read_delim("../meta_data/gene_names.txt",delim="\t")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   gene_id = col_character(),
##   gene_symbol = col_character()
## )
